tags.description: The Pines is a rustic campground in a wooded setting, located adjacent to Barbour's Creek, a stocked trout stream. Most of the campsites are designed for tents, but small recreation vehicles can be accommodated.
tags.name: The Pines Campground
tags.operator: National Forest Service Eastern Divide Ranger District: 540-552-4641

tags.description: Hopper Creek Group Campground offers a shaded and rustic atmosphere for group tent camping with an open area for activities and a large campfire ring for evening gatherings. Only one group can reserve the area at a time.
tags.name: Hopper Creek Group Campground
tags.note: March 15 through November 30 No trailers, pop-ups, or RV's. Tent camping only. No drinking water available Vault toilet
tags.operator: US Forest Service, George Washington & Jefferson National Forests, Glenwood and Pedlar Ranger Districts

tags.description: Campfires are allowed in designated campfire rings at each campsite. Dead and down wood can be gathered on site.
tags.name: Cave Mountain Lake Campground
tags.note: Early April through late October Alcoholic beverages prohibited in day use area. No boats or watercraft of any kind allowed on lake. Drinking water available Flush toilets with warm water showers
